    <item>
      <title>Creation</title>
      <link>https://vishvAsa.github.io/notes/computing/content/video/creation/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://vishvAsa.github.io/notes/computing/content/video/creation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;procedure&#34;&gt;Procedure&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;List the points you want to make. Keep the material to be presented ready, in proper sequence. Perhaps make a slide deck.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Rehearse once mentally.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Always make a short test video to check audio/ video quality for clarity, lag etc..&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Present.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Edit as needed. Good preparation avoids this (oft frustrating) step to the maximum extant possible.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;recorders&#34;&gt;Recorders&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;spreadsheet&#34; src=&#34;recorder.toml&#34; fullHeightWithRowsPerScreen=8&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;obs-studio&#34;&gt;OBS Studio&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Set up video capture devices (camera 1, camera 2, screen capture, window capture &amp;hellip;)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Set up audio capture devices (output, input). Best input device - mic.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;editors&#34;&gt;Editors&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;spreadsheet&#34; src=&#34;editor.toml&#34; fullHeightWithRowsPerScreen=8&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;kdenlive&#34;&gt;Kdenlive&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Shift R&lt;/code&gt; for cutting&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Filters for fixing high bass audio -&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Youtube</title>
      <link>https://vishvAsa.github.io/notes/computing/content/video/youtube/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://vishvAsa.github.io/notes/computing/content/video/youtube/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;metadata&#34;&gt;Metadata&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Title up to 100 characters.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;table-of-contents&#34;&gt;Table of contents&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Description can have table of contents, which show up as chapters (even in transcript).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Example&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Source: &lt;a href=&#34;http://youtube.com/watch?v=QScX0AsEPUM&#34;&gt;TW&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;2&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;3&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;4&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;5&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;6&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;7&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f&#34;&gt;8&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-markdown&#34; data-lang=&#34;markdown&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;00:00 - mangalam  &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;00:40 - Intro, context  &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;02:27 - Bharathan/ azhagiyavaradar, a vAnamAmalai shiShya?!  &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;03:30 - vyAsa&amp;#39;s &lt;span style=&#34;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;**mahAbhArata**&lt;/span&gt; - kRShNa as dUta in udyoga-parva, refuses duryodhana, bhIShma, droNa food, takes vidura food.  &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;04:45 - shAstri-vAvilla recension verses - &lt;span style=&#34;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;**duryodhana**&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;s objection  &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;08:30 - &lt;span style=&#34;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;**kRShNa&amp;#39;s response**&lt;/span&gt; - commitment to dharma, no Apat - won&amp;#39;t accept food from haters.  &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;11:45 - vidura&amp;#39;s reaction.  &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;12:50 - &lt;span style=&#34;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;**lokAchArya**&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;comment-handling&#34;&gt;Comment handling&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;best-practice&#34;&gt;Best practice&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;For controvertial videos - hold and moderate comments. Don&amp;rsquo;t platform abusive and spammy commenters.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Collate and answer comments at some safe place (eg. the top level or external page), perhaps with a link to the triggering comment.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Post a link to this comment as a response to the triggering comment; or just say - &amp;ldquo;Answered as a top level comment&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;problems&#34;&gt;Problems&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;When a (abusive/ spammy?) commentor is hidden or his post deleted, response is not hidden.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;By default YT only shows &amp;ldquo;Top&amp;rdquo; comments, and not &amp;ldquo;all&amp;rdquo; comments (which the viewer has to manually select.)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Deleting a repeated comment was observed to delete an unintended comment 20260402.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;review&#34;&gt;Review&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;YT studio has a good interface for handling comments.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Useful filters&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
